  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Automation Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Support automation activities during project execution, including site-based implementation and commissioning support.</p></li><li><p>Assist in reviewing and closing out I/O checks and loop testing activities in line with approved qualification protocols.</p></li><li><p>Participate in control system configuration and testing activities (e.g. DeltaV), under guidance from senior engineers.</p></li><li><p>Prepare, update, and maintain project and qualification documentation, including pre-execution and post-execution records.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with engineering, quality, and commissioning teams to track outstanding actions and ensure timely closure of deliverables.</p></li><li><p>Support troubleshooting activities during testing and execution phases.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Electrical, Instrumentation, Automation, Chemical Engineering, or related disciplines.</p></li><li><p>Exposure to automation systems or control systems in a manufacturing or project environment is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Basic understanding of testing, commissioning, or qualification activities (I/O checks, loop checks, FAT/SAT) preferred.</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working on-site and in fast-paced project environments.</p></li><li><p>Good documentation skills and willingness to learn GMP / regulated project practices.</p></li></ul>",
